product_name: Benefit CosmeticsThe POREfessional Blurring & Smoothing Foundation with Niacinamide
summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsSustainable PackagingBenefit's The POREfessional Blurring & Smoothing Foundation with Niacinamide is a smoothing, blurring, non-comedogenic foundation with medium, weightless coverage, with niacinamide that improves look of your pores & skin over time.

reviews.headline: Go-to every day base!
reviews.comments: This foundation is wonderfully smoothing and blurring (plus it's acne safe w/ no fragrance!). It builds very well and looks great over texture and wrinkles. It doesn't cake up around my nose or dry up and crack by the end of the day. I use a beauty sponge to apply and do not powder or use a setting spray. I have combo/dry, 40+ skin for reference. The only note is that the shades are odd. I am fair or fair to light cool and 9C (light to med cool) matches me perfectly. The lighter cool and neutral shades are extremely pale or yellow or have an odd undertone. I rotate between this and the Lawless Forget the Filler foundation for every day, although I find Lawless to be more smoothing.

reviews.headline: I would buy this item again.
reviews.comments: this looks so nice when you put it on.    Had lots of help picking out a color etc at Ulta and really appreciated the help.   Brittany in Brow Dept and Benefit section was a great help.

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: I have fair cool skin with normal texture. This foundation sits really strangely on my skin- almost like it refuses to blend in. I tried a brush and a beauty blender, primer and no primer, setting powder and none. Won't buy again.

reviews.headline: Natural look
reviews.comments: First time trying this foundation and so far I like it. It gives me a very natural look. I do feel it a bit oily. But love the look.

reviews.headline: Wait for it
reviews.comments: I didn't like this when I first put it on, I thought it highlighted my pores and textures, pretty much the opposite of what I was hoping it would do, but I let it sit for a few minutes and soon I couldn't even tell I had anything on. The formula actually reminds me a lot of the Pretty Vulgar foundation, but with better shade range. So if you ever tried and liked Pretty Vulgar foundation, you'll like this. Just give it a few minutes to settle first.

reviews.headline: For some skin types, not all.
reviews.comments: This foundation has great coverage, just a little foundation does the job to cover my pink/redish skin. It is not for oily skin though, after 5 hours it looks like I sprayed some cooking oil onto my face. If you have a bruises, tattoos, dark circles, spots, this foundation is perfect for you but not so much for texture skin. I feel as if this foundation made my pores more noticeable.

reviews.headline: Excellent at blurring and smoothing
reviews.comments: I really like how this foundation settles over time. It really does blur and smooth. Also one pump goes a long way. I appreciate that this isn't watery or drying on the skin. The smell is a bit strong when you put it on (a bit chemically) but doesn't last long. By the time I have finished the rest of my makeup I can't even smell it anymore.

reviews.headline: Recommend
reviews.comments: This foundation is good for everyday wear and has great ingredients (niacinamide, rose hip extract, and glycerin). However, the shade range  is lacking.

reviews.headline: It's ok
reviews.comments: Not good for super oily gals. Drys too fast leading to applying more. Too thick

reviews.headline: Great foundation!
reviews.comments:
I like this foundation so much! It stayed on through 8.5 hours of work and a 3 hour band practice, and I only needed a touch of powder and a setting spray refresh during the day. It remains matte to the touch and is transfer proof.

The only thing I want to note is that the shades are actually way darker in real life. I was excited that they had such a wide range of shades with different undertones as someone with very fair skin who struggles to find a good shade match, but when I actually looked at them everything except the lightest shade was too dark for me. And I'm definitely not even as pale as the models for 1C and 5C. I hope they get the shades more accurate in the future.

reviews.headline: It's Ok
reviews.comments: I'll start by saying I don't wear foundation often and picked this shade based on what shade I wore in another brand.  It's a little too warm/orange for me, but that's fixable with a color corrector.  My real problem is I have to use three different cleansers to get this stuff off my face at the end of the day.  Even the Benefit oil-based cleanser they were offering as a free gift with purchase does not remove this product on its own; I had to use a second oil-based cleanser plus my regular facewash; and my towels are still covered in makeup.  I guess in a way that could be a seen as a positive, since it stays put all day long.  If you are 40+ like me, make sure you moisturize and use a good primer/setting spray to stop it from settling into fine lines. I don't feel like going through the hassle off returning so I will keep this and use it for special occasions only; and stick to tinted moisturizer for everyday wear. Overall, I do like the way it looks on me despite all my complaints.

reviews.headline: Super oily skin girl
reviews.comments: I am a super oily skin girl and i tried this because a influencer on tiktok had me convenced it would be amazing. Needless to say it doesnt stay all day and my face is super oily so i figured it would help but i guess with this being a "blurring and smoothing" line i should have expected that i just really wanted to love this product and im sad!

reviews.headline: I would  not buy again
reviews.comments: It's thick's and shows the thickness on your face.  I would not recommend.

reviews.headline: looks so fake
reviews.comments: this foundation is like 2010 finish,  matte, heavy on skin, maybe it could work if you have super oily skin

reviews.headline: Not good for dry skin
reviews.comments: Probably great if you uave oily skin. I tend to be dry and it was hard to blend out and it made my dry spots worse.

reviews.headline: Not for dry skin
reviews.comments: I wanted to love this so much. The color match is perfect! It covers any blemishes or dark spots well! But it's horrendous to blend well and i have combo skin and any dry spots it clings to and sometimes pills on. I have a great skin case base and ive tried it with a  primer and without and same results with or without one. This product will probably be fine if you have oiley skin but if you're in any way even slightly dry, there are SO many better options so dont believe the social media hype!!

reviews.headline: Full coverage foundation - Texture is just right.
reviews.comments: I didn't expect to like it this much. Many new foundation came out with such light and thin texture and blended to nothing on the skin. This foundation has enough thickness that truly gives you full coverage and perfect skin on my normal skin.

reviews.headline: Perfect foundation for combination skin.
reviews.comments: I absolutely love this foundation. At age 47 had totally given up on foundation. my skin has gotten bigger pores. This foundation stays put in the heat, for a swim, and feels so lite. looks natural. even though my skin is more on the dryer side, this foundation is just soooo great. I had tried Estee Lauder, Too Faced, Urban Decay, ans Lorreal Infallible. None of them stay put and covered my poores like this foundation. reviews.headline: WOW!
reviews.comments: I am sooo picky and this blew me away! I love everything about it, but the blurring is real and so is the skincare! My face after two weeks is smoother and brighter. Benefit has always had really good foundations, but they discontinue so much and it makes me sad! Keep this one! Im hooked!

faceoff_positive.comments: I only got to try this foundation once so far - in shade 26C Hero, which was way too dark for my light-medium cool-toned skin - but honestly, I was still kind of blown away. I'm already planning to get shade-matched in store once it's available because I need to wear this properly. Right after applying, I could tell the texture was different - in a good way. It went on super smooth and felt really lightweight, almost like a tinted moisturizer but with way more coverage than I expected. I have combination skin (a bit oily in the T-zone and drier around the edges), and this somehow managed to sit beautifully across all of it without clinging or sliding. I finished it off with setting spray like I usually do, and I didn't have to touch it the rest of the day. What surprised me most was how blurred and soft my skin looked right away - especially around my nose and pores, which are usually the first to act up with any foundation. It didn't sink into lines or highlight texture, and it felt comfortable the whole time I wore it. Even after hours, it still looked good and didn't transfer. Since I've only used it once, I can't speak to the long-term skin benefits yet (like the niacinamide, rose hip, or glycerin effects), but just from that one wear, my skin did look smoother even after I washed it off. No breakouts either, which is huge for me - my skin can be reactive. All in all, I didn't think I'd be this excited about a foundation that doesn't even match me (yet). Can't wait to try it again in my right shade - it might be the one.

faceoff_negative.comments:
This foundation claims to be a smoothing, blurring, noncomedogenic foundation with medium, weightless coverage and niacinamide that improves the look of your pores and skin over time.

The shade I chose is too light for me so that's a bummer, am I going to buy the right shade based on my review‚Ä¶ no probably not. This foundation is good, but I like others better. Yes, it is both smoothing and blurring, but the claim that is smooths skin overtime; I just don't want to wear this for 30 days straight to find out. 

This leans on the heavier coverage side of medium and that's not my preference I prefer something lighter. I do think when you look at this applied it's definitely apparent that you are wearing foundation so if you want something that "melts into the skin" this isn't the foundation to choose. I don't know if this is buildable because when I first tried this I used a sponge and the amount I applied was too much and it looked cakey. For my preferences, I use a sponge and not even one pump, I apply a very thin layer. I couldn't imagine applying another layer, I don't think I would like it. This did start to break up on my chin after 3.5 hrs which surprised me‚Ä¶ but it is very hot and humid where I live.

In summary, if I mix in bronzing drops (my fault for bad shade selection), and apply a very thin layer this does look nice, it does smooth and blur the pores as claimed. This foundation does have a natural matte finish  as stated. And in the heat and humidity of summer starts to break up on my chin at the 3.5 hour mark, if I use a little powder at that time it helps, the rest of the face is good. My skin tends to be a little dry, so I use only a small amount of powder on my face to set, the powder just isn't needed with the natural matte finish. Lastly, the foundation did not irritate my skin or cause breakouts so that's definitely a plus.
faceoff_negative.headline: This is good, not great
